    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-04T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-04T08:30:00-05:00" n="182"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_SAE1">S/AE</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>No. 182 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minutes of a Meeting of the Combined Policy Committee</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d182fn1">See <ref target="#d619fn1">document No. 619,
                            footnote 1</ref>, for information on the creation of this
                        Committee.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1945-07-04T09:30:00-04:00">July 4, 1945, 9:30 a.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d182fn2">For a list of the
                            persons present at this meeting and for another extract from the
                            minutes, see <ref target="#d619">document No. 619</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Minutes of Combined Policy Committee Meeting Held at the
                        Pentagon on July</hi> 4<hi rend="smallcaps">th</hi>, 1945—9:30 <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">a.m.</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p rend="center">3. <hi rend="smallcaps">use of weapon against third parties</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">
                        <persName corresp="#p_WFMSHM1">Field Marshal Wilson</persName>
                    </hi> stated that the British Government concurred in the use of the <gloss
                        target="#t_TA1">T. A.</gloss> weapon against <persName corresp="#p_J1"
                        >Japan</persName>. He added that the Prime Minister might wish to discuss
                    this matter with the President at the forthcoming meeting in Berlin.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d182fn3">Secretary of War <persName corresp="#p_SHL1"
                            >Stimson</persName> also discussed at this meeting the possibility that
                            <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> might wish to speak to
                            <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName> at the Berlin Conference
                        about the development and use of a new atomic weapon. See <ref
                            target="#d619">document No. 619</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BHH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi> H <hi rend="smallcaps">Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roger Makins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Joint Secretaries</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
